    "body": "The Checker Framework is a static analysis tool for Java. It provides type-checking for Java code. The Checker Framework's qualifiers package contains annotations that are used to specify the types of values that can be assigned to variables. These annotations are used by the Checker Framework to perform type-checking on Java code.\n\nThe `ApiSurface` class is used to generate a surface of classes that are allowed to be used in the GCP API. The `pruningPattern` method is used to exclude specific classes and packages from the allowed set of packages. The inclusion of the Checker Framework's qualifiers package ensures that all necessary classes and methods for using the Checker Framework are included in the API surface.\n\nThis commit adds a new pruning pattern, `.pruningPattern(\"org[.]checkerframework[.].*[.]qual[.].*\")`, after line 8 in three different files: `DirectRunnerApiSurfaceTest`, `GcpCoreApiSurfaceTest`, and `GcpApiSurfaceTest`. This pruning pattern excludes classes from the Checker Framework's qualifiers package, which is a part of the Java platform and not part of the GCP API."
