    "body": "The `Form#onSubmit()` method is responsible for handling form submissions. By default, it calls `validate()` to validate the form and update the model if there is only one button. If there are more than one buttons, it calls the `onClick()` method for the button which submitted the form.\n\nThis commit refactors this behavior to handle multiple buttons by calling `onClick()` directly from `Form#onSubmit()`. This simplifies the logic and makes it easier to understand.\n\nThis change does not affect any existing behavior and should not cause any issues."
}

